title: Lost world DISCOVERED: Staggering images of newly-found cave captured in Vietnam
text:
Lost world DISCOVERED: Staggering images of newly-found cave captured in Vietnam Lost world DISCOVERED: Staggering images of newly-found cave captured in Vietnam WE'VE all dreamed of finding lost worlds but this photographer actually found one when he stumbled across a newly discovered cave and caught it all on camera. PUBLISHED: 14:07, Fri, Sep 11, 2015 | UPDATED: 15:05, Fri, Sep 11, 2015 CATERS Tour guides in the newly found cave in Vietnam 
The jaw-dropping pictures were snapped by adventure photographer Ryan Deboodt, 32, after the cave was discovered for the first time by locals just one month ago. 
The cave is located near Vietnam's Phong Nha Ke Bang National Park and is believed to be an extension of a previously discovered cave called Hang Tien. 
Ryan said: "It was a really amazing feeling to find a completely new cave. "Being in big caves is truly otherworldly. 
The darkness descends around you and nothing seems familiar. "I love the feeling of not knowing what lies ahead. It feels like I'm on another planet with the darkness of space all around me. CATERS/RYAN DEBOODT Weve all dreamt of finding lost worlds but this photographer actually found one CATERS/RYAN DEBOODT The cave was discovered for the first time by locals just one month ago 
During the formation of the cave, the walls became scalloped due to water running through creating beautiful waves of white and black.Ryan said: "We had to trek through lots of inter-connecting caves to reach this hidden one - traversing through dense jungle and over razor sharp limestone rocks."It started with a long car ride followed by a two hour trek through pouring rain before we finally had to pass through the Hang Tien to reach our final, hidden, destination. CATERS/RYAN DEBOODT The cave is located near Vietnams Phong Nha Ke Bang National Park CATERS/RYAN DEBOODT The cave is believed to be an extension of a previously discovered cave 
"The walls and ceiling of the cave were nearly perfectly horizontal with stripes of black and white limestone."The floors of this cave are also very interesting as the main passage is covered in small gours that go on for hundreds of meters." CATERS/RYANDEBOODT Photographer Ryan spoke of the amazing experience CATERS/RYANDEBOODT
